summary: Don’t forget Natasha Romanoff
body:
Don’t forget Natasha Romanoff

Don’t forget the woman who fell to her death so Clint would have a chance to see his family again

Don’t forget the woman who joined S.H.I.E.L.D to wipe the red from her ledger and ended up saving the world

Don’t forget the woman who refused to move on because the Avengers was the only family she ever had

Don’t forget the woman who sacrificed her life because she believed it would bring her family back, even if it would mean never seeing them again

Natasha Romanoff fell to her death not knowing whether she would save everyone, and yet she did it anyway because it was the only hope she had.

Remember her.

summary: Okay so I have a question about the 5 year time skip in Endgame and how the works with the people brought back.  Like Peter is...
body:
Okay so I have a question about the 5 year time skip in Endgame and how the works with the people brought back. 

Like Peter is still 16 but he must have classmates who survived the snap and are in college now. 

I can just imagine conversations like this: “Where is Amy?” “Oh she survived the snap, she’s in college now, she graduated like 3 years ago”

Or, “Billy what are you doing in my math class, you’re 11″ “Yeah I was 11 5 years ago, now I’m 16 because I survived the snap.” “Oh… weird.”

Or what about siblings where the younger one survived the snap and the older one didn’t and so then when they were brought back they’re now younger than their sibling.
